The paper deals with scheduling and routing in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses mathematical analysis and simulations, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and multiagent systems (cs.MA).
